source:
[1] 5_linux_socket_More on headers and APIs.pdf.xoj

note:

[1] a sample of the client socket call flow:

	socket()
	connect()
	while(x) {
		write()
		read()
	}
	close()

[2] a sample of the server socket call flow

	socket()
	bind()
	listen()
	// connect()	// not used!!
	while(1){
		accept()
		while(x) {
			// notice, they are different order than the client
			read()
			write()
		}
		close()
	}
	close()
